

NAME
rlogind - Remote login server
SYNOPSIS
rlogind
[,OPTION/...]
DESCRIPTION
Remote login server

-4, --ipv4
daemon mode only accepts IPv4

-6, --ipv6
only IPv6 in daemon mode

-a, --verify-hostname
ask hostname for verification

-d, --daemon[=,MAX/]
daemon mode, with instance limit

-D, --debug[=,LEVEL/]
set debug level

-l, --no-rhosts
ignore .rhosts file

-L, --local-domain=,NAME/
set local domain name

-n, --no-keepalive
do not set SO_KEEPALIVE

-o, --allow-root
allow uid 0 to login, disabled by default

-p, --port=,PORT/
listen on given port (valid only in daemon mode)

-r, --reverse-required
require reverse resolving of a remote host IP

-?, --help
give this help list

--usage
give a short usage message

-V, --version
print program version

Mandatory or optional arguments to long options are also mandatory or optional
for any corresponding short options.
